This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   The user asked to add a new fictional "PulseBoard" channel plugin to OpenClaw. Requirements:
   - PulseBoard is an imaginary real-time bulletin board messaging platform where users post messages to named "boards" (prefixed with `!`) and can send direct messages (bare usernames)
   - Support both direct and group chat types
   - 4000-character text chunk limit
   - Follow the same extension structure as existing channel plugins (IRC, Nostr, Telegram)
   - Do NOT modify any existing files — only create new files in `extensions/pulseboard/`
   - First read `PLAN.md`, then execute the plan

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - OpenClaw channel plugin extension architecture (`extensions/` directory, bundled workspace plugin tree)
   - `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` public subpaths — the only valid import surface for extension code
   - Plugin naming invariants: `@openclaw/<id>` package name, dir == manifest id, npmSpec == package name, channel.id == manifest id (enforced by `src/plugins/bundled-plugin-naming.test.ts`)
   - `defineChannelPluginEntry` / `defineSetupPluginEntry` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core`
   - `createChatChannelPlugin` for composing the full channel plugin with security, pairing, outbound
   - `createPluginRuntimeStore` for the runtime store pattern
   - `buildChannelConfigSchema` + Zod for config schema
   - `createScopedChannelConfigAdapter`, `createScopedDmSecurityResolver`, `adaptScopedAccountAccessor` for config helpers
   - `createComputedAccountStatusAdapter` + `createDefaultChannelRuntimeState` for status
   - `ChannelSetupWizard` + `ChannelSetupAdapter` for the setup wizard
   - `createAccountStatusSink` returns a **function** `(patch: Omit<ChannelAccountSnapshot, "accountId">) => void` (not an object)
   - `getChatChannelMeta` only works with pre-registered `ChatChannelId`s — new channels must define meta inline
   - `ChannelMeta` type accessible from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-runtime`
   - `chunkTextForOutbound` is not in any public subpath; `chunker` field is optional in `ChannelOutboundAdapter`

3. Files and Code Sections:
   - **`extensions/pulseboard/package.json`** — Package metadata; naming invariants satisfied: `name: "@openclaw/pulseboard"`, `channel.id: "pulseboard"`, `install.npmSpec: "@openclaw/pulseboard"`

   - **`extensions/pulseboard/openclaw.plugin.json`** — Plugin manifest: `id: "pulseboard"`, `channels: ["pulseboard"]`

   - **`extensions/pulseboard/index.ts`**:
     ```ts
     import type { ChannelPlugin } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
     import { defineChannelPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
     import { pulseboardPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
     import { setPulseboardRuntime } from "./src/runtime.js";
     export { pulseboardPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
     export { setPulseboardRuntime } from "./src/runtime.js";
     export default defineChannelPluginEntry({
       id: "pulseboard", name: "PulseBoard", description: "PulseBoard channel plugin",
       plugin: pulseboardPlugin as ChannelPlugin, setRuntime: setPulseboardRuntime,
     });
     ```

   - **`extensions/pulseboard/setup-entry.ts`**:
     ```ts
     import { defineSetupPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
     import { pulseboardPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
     export default defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseboardPlugin);
     ```

   - **`extensions/pulseboard/api.ts`**:
     ```ts
     export * from "./src/accounts.js";
     export * from "./src/setup-surface.js";
     ```

   - **`extensions/pulseboard/src/types.ts`** — Core types; imports `DmPolicy`, `GroupPolicy`, `OpenClawConfig` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/config-runtime`; imports `BaseProbeResult` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-runtime`:
